postcontent:
That's a Military & Police Model of 1902, First Change,6 shot,4 inches barrel.. This gun was in production until 1905. It seems to be in pretty good shape for its age. The  number  is #  262**

The Military & Police revolver line is S&W's most successful model, from 1899. The design evolved from year to year, and there are variations involving grip shape, barrel length, and lockwork design, but it is basically the same gun all the way through.. 

The .38 U.S. SERVICE CTG,S mentioned in the stamping is the .38. 

Nice gun, safe to shoot with standard ammo. Do not shoot +P ammo in this revolver. It won't blow up in your hand, but the steel is softer and lots of high-pressure rounds will just enable wear and tear that the gun does not need. $ 450. Firm  text REDACTED

Fits Glock models 19/23/32/38 (Gen 1, 2, or 3; NOT Gen 4).  The model number is LMS-1131P and outputs a pulsating red beam.  The laser fits inside the Glock’s frame by replacing the stock guide rod/recoil spring assembly.  Installation takes less than two minutes and does not permanently change the weapon. Completely internal! Keep your current holster for your GLOCK, keep your tactical lights, keep your favorite grips.

Extremely rugged. The LaserMax Guide Rod Laser for GLOCK meets or exceeds both Mil-Spec and Homeland Security durability test standards (drop tests, blowing sand, temperature and humidity extremes, salt water fog, deep water immersion, 20,000+ rounds live fire).
